-- Nordic Stocks Retreat: Finnair, Sweco, Sponda, Hexagon Shares Are Active
-- Alexis Xydias
-- 2010-07-07T08:22:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-07/nordic-stocks-retreat-finnair-sweco-sponda-hexagon-shares-are-active.html

          
          
             The  Stoxx Nordic 30 Index , the
benchmark measure for the region, fell 55.52, or 0.9 percent, to
6,279.82 as of 10:18 a.m. in Stockholm, after yesterday posting
its biggest gain in five weeks.  
 The  OMX Stockholm 30 Index  lost 0.6 percent and the
 Copenhagen 20 Index  retreated 0.5 percent. The  Helsinki 25 Index 
fell 1.2 percent and Norway’s  OBX Index  dropped 0.8 percent.  
 The following companies’ shares were among the most active
in Nordic markets today. Symbols are in parentheses.  
      Finnair Oyj  (FIA1S FH) climbed 3.2 percent to 4.22 euros,
set for its fourth gain. The Finnish largest airline said its
flight passenger load factor was 75.6 percent in June as it saw
“significant” growth in its Asian traffic unit.  
 Hexagon AB  (HEXAB SS) soared 7.7 percent to 109.2 kronor,
its second gain this week. The world’s biggest maker of
measuring instruments agreed to buy U.S.-based Intergraph
Corp. for $2.13 billion to add software that helps companies
visualize complex data and design factories, ships and oilrigs,
it said in a statement today.  
 Sponda Oyj  (SDA1V FH) jumped 4.6 percent to 2.72 euros, set
for its highest level since June 23. Finland’s largest publicly
traded real-estate company was raised to “buy” from “hold”
at SEB Enskilda.  
 Sweco AB  (SWECB SS) advanced 2.3 percent to 49.8 kronor,
extending yesterday’s 0.6 percent gain. The Swedish engineering
consultant said the company’s engineers had been contracted to
study and plan the development of a new railway station in
Malmoe, Sweden.  
